{"key":"processedPost-15310510","value":{"id":15310510,"first":15309473,"last":16156618,"when":1320199375,"utime":"11/02/11 05:02 AM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />Oh well you can also submerge it, that should not be the problem I think... </blockquote><br />I wouldn't submerge a bulk substrate mid-flush.&nbsp; There's too much risk of over-saturation and also of breaking it when you empty the water.<br />The answer to your question is don't dunk mid flush, but as has been posted many times in the past as well as just above, pour water around the edges of the substrate.&nbsp; If you don't overdo it, the water will absorb into the substrate overnight.&nbsp; After 12 hours or so, pour off any excess that hasn't soaked in.<br />RR"}}